column5: Just booked a cottage there for the July long weekend.  Quick Interweb search tells me bass and pike in abundance.  Anyone been there before?

I was there once, fished an afternoon caught some small and largemouth bass, I don't think there are any pike in there. (I know pike are usually everwhere).There was rainbow stocking a while back but doubt there are any left. Check out the backroad's mapbook it will tell you what's in that lake for sure.
I have fished Kapakog which empties into Healey (or vice versa).  Kapakog does have pike seems to be mostly about 4lbs in size.  Lots of Bass.  Healey should not be that different.

I know there are good bass in there, both largies and smallies. Never caught any pike but am told they are there too. Also some of the biggest crappies I have ever seen, but got them in the winter. Great, now i'm hungry.
Har.. Ismael, welcome aboard matey! How's Cap'n Ahab? Still chasin' Ole Whitey?
Thanks for the info guys...  "There she blows!--there she blows! A hump like a snow-hill! It is Moby Dick!"
